    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect DCI format handling in nr_ue_process_dci_indication_pdu\n\n### Summary\nWhen processing DCI indications in `nr_ue_process_dci_indication_pdu()`, the function was not properly handling unsupported DCI format cases. This led to unexpected behavior where invalid DCI formats would not be correctly rejected, potentially causing issues with RNTI type handling and DCI processing.\n\nThe fix ensures that all unsupported DCI format cases explicitly return `NR_DCI_NONE`, preventing any undefined behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_procedures.c`: Added explicit `return NR_DCI_NONE;` in the default case of `nr_extract_dci_info()` to properly handle unsupported DCI formats.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Send a DCI indication with an unsupported format (not `NFAPI_NR_FORMAT_0_0_AND_1_0` or `NFAPI_NR_FORMAT_0_1_AND_1_1`)\n2. Observe that the function may not properly return `NR_DCI_NONE` as expected\n3. This can lead to incorrect DCI processing or unexpected behavior in the MAC layer\n\nThe fix ensures consistent behavior by explicitly handling all error cases.\n"
}